textBeforeTable: The class of the device determines the speed at which GPRS can be used. The table below displays different types of technologies and their rates of transfer. Comparison of Technologies Mobile phones of this class are attached to either GPRS or GSM voice service. One needs to switch manually between services. Class C Mobile phones of this class can be attached to both GPRS and GSM services, but using only one service at a time. Switching between them (suspend/resume) is done automatically. Class B GSM services simultaneously. Mobile phones of this class can be connected to both GPRS and Class A There are three GPRS classes which help indicate the capabilities of a mobile phone. GPRS Classes For a more complete list, see Nokia: What You Can Do With GPRS. GPRS provides the ability to make use many different mobile services and capabilities, for example e-mail, web browsing, games, calendar funcionality, using the cell phone as modem for laptops. instant messaging and lots more.
